Tomato Barbecue Baby Back Betty A. Swanigan

Rating: 4
We've made this recipe about 20 times. Sometimes we follow the recipe exactly, sometimes we make it spicier with cayenne pepper, hot sauce, etc. But most of the time we stick to the recipe. Everybody always love the ribs. Super easy and always good - can't beat that with a stick (or a rib).

Rating: 4
Can't believe it was so easy and this good! I wouldn't change a thing!

Rating: 0
I don't like ketchup so I used San Marzano tomatoes, peeled and seeded, sauteed the onions and garlic in EVO, then added the tomatoes and the rest of the ingredients. I let it boil for 15 minutes then simmered for 30 and then cooled and put it in the blender. Everyone loved it. I also put a rub on the ribs, pre-cooked them without the sauce for 20 minutes in the oven - then grilled and added the sauce.

Rating: 4
Excellent! Very easy and taste just like restaurant quality. I followed the recipe exactly.

Rating: 3
Easy to put together and one guest said they were the best ribs he's ever had. I added about 2/3 cup Asian Chili sauce, with a fair amount of hot to it...balanced out the sweet (which I think was totally sweet enough). I'd made these again as they were so fast and easy!

Rating: 3
I made these for Mother's Day dinner, and everyone loved them. However, I played with the sauce a little. I had doubled the recipe to make sure there was enough for the table, bumped up the pepper by another teaspoon. This was fine for me, it had a nice kick, but I didn't think my parents would enjoy it, so I added a can of tomato puree before running it through the food processor. It gave the sauce a nice flavor, definitely tamed the heat. I'll make this again, next time follow the recipe and see how it comes out.

Rating: 3
Filled my need for a fast rib recipe and my family's need for tasty bbq. Used spareribs, didn't puree the sauce, re-sauced upon taking off the foil. Made 80% on the grill and 20% in the oven; all agreed that the grilled ribs were superior! Served with mac & cheese, black bean & corn salad, cooked greens and an A. Rafanelli Zinfandel for a wonderful New Year's Eve meal. It was happy cooking and happy eating!

