Rating: 4
This recipe, as the description states, is not overly sweet. My husband liked it exactly this way; I might prefer a bit of extra sweetness by adding extra sugar or honey next time. Because it uses so much pepper, use only freshly ground pepper, and it won't seem like too much (as I thought it might). I pureed it as directed, but I don't see any harm in omitting that step, so I might be tempted to skip that next time! But DO use HEAVY-weight aluminum foil to line the pan. Cleanup was a bit more challenging without it b/c cooking juices still managed to go through.

