Rating: 3
Very delicious and easy, even with my embarassing substitutions (thought I had all the ingredients, but...). No molasses, so upped the brown sugar and used maple syrup. Malt instead of cider vinegar. Tossed in a little Trader Joe's Mole. Otherwise, followed the recipe, and it was delicious!

Rating: 3
Great starter recipe. One thing to note: For all of you who have never done ribs without boiling first, the first hour of being covered tightly is basically the same thing. The ribs steam in order to make them more fall-of-the-bone tender. I've never really been a fan of this method, but with this recipe, I liked it. Some modifications - red pepper flakes, 1-2 chipotles (canned), with some of the adobo sauce, and I didn't puree the sauce. Pull em out of the pan, put 'em on the grill, and pour the sauce over them for the last hour. Yum!

